<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>do someone in the eye • hit someone in the eye</xh5><p> <i>do someone in the eye</i>—(sl.) cheat or defraud a person: He handed her a gold chain of curious workmanship. “Unless I’ve been <u>done in the eye</u> it’s an old one.”</p><p><i>hit someone in the eye—</i>1. make a strong impact on smb.: I drove about in a smart red-wheeled coach. Anyhow, it <u>hit</u> my colleagues badly <u>in the eye</u>. 2. give a person a shock: Modern young men’s manners now really quite <u>hit you in the eye</u>.</p> </entry>
